FBIS3-633 "drafr048_d_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola UN Human Rights Commission Condemns UNITA LD1003160494 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 1500 GMT 10 Mar 94 LD1003160494 Lisbon Radio Renascenca Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] The UN Human Rights Commission in Geneva has condenmed UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence of Angola]. A resolution was approved which blames UNITA totally for the situation in Angola. [passage omitted] The Angolan Government has welcomed this resolution. The Angolan representative, Ambassador Eduardo Parreira, has expressed his satisfaction and said that perhaps it is time to stir the conscience of the less aware. [Begin Parreira recording] I believe that this resolution will be like a reference point which, like a beacon, illuminates the spirit of those who still have not understood that the war is indeed a tradegy, one of the...[pauses] The worst of human rights violations and that it is taking us nowhere. The doors are open for dialogue -- they have always been -- and in the Bicesse accords and in subsequent meetings we have always had and have fought for a spirit of concord and dialogue. [end recording] [passage omitted]
